A Node.js and Express web application using EJS templates, created for Lab 5 (Parts Aâ€“E).
The site is a zombie-themed drinks shop that allows users to browse products, register, search, complete surveys and view shop locations.


Project Overview:

The Caffeine Zombies web app demonstrates how to use Express routing, EJS templates, and forms to build a simple but dynamic multi-page website.


How to Run Locally

Install dependencies:
npm init
npm install express
npm install ejs

Then start the server using:
node index.js

Then Browse the pages using following links:
https://www.doc.gold.ac.uk/usr/261/ â†’ Home

/about â†’ About the shop

/search â†’ Search drinks

/register â†’ Register form

/survey â†’ Customer survey

